<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3121] Watermark forwarding does not work for sources not producing any data</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3121</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This mailing list discussion explains the issue in detail: &lt;a href=&quot;http://apache-flink-user-mailing-list-archive.2336050.n4.nabble.com/Custom-TimestampExtractor-and-FlinkKafkaConsumer082-td3488.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://apache-flink-user-mailing-list-archive.2336050.n4.nabble.com/Custom-TimestampExtractor-and-FlinkKafkaConsumer082-td3488.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a workaround for now, the Kafka source can emit a final watermark for sources not producing any data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
